author: Erica Werner, Ap Congressional Correspondent
title: Prospective speakers multiply in House as all wait on Ryan
text: Photo: J. Scott Applewhite, AP FILE - In this June 24, 2011 file photo, Rep. Paul Ryan, R-Wis., right, and Rep. Bill Flores, R-Texas, walk to the House floor on Capitol Hill in Washington. Every day another Republican lawmaker seems to wake up and decide that he _ and in at least one case, she _ would make a pretty good speaker of the House. WASHINGTON (AP) — Every day another Republican lawmaker seems to wake up and decide that he — and in at least one case, she — might make a pretty good speaker of the House.
